problem: Find an ordered pair $(x,y)$ that solves the system: \begin{align*} 2x - 3y &= -3.2 - 0.2x + 0.1y,\\ x &= 0.6x - y + 8.8 \end{align*}
solution: First, we organize each equation by getting the variables on one side and the constants on the other.  This makes our equations $2.2x -3.1y = -3.2$ and $0.4x + y = 8.8$. Solving the second equation for $y$ in terms of $x$ gives $y = 8.8-0.4x$.  Substituting this into our other equation gives \begin{align*}&2.2x - 3.1(8.8-0.4x) = -3.2 \\ &2.2x -27.28 + 1.24x =-3.2 \\ &3.44x = 24.08 \\ &x = 7. \end{align*}So, $y = 8.8-0.4x = 6$, and our solution is $(x,y) = \boxed{(7,6)}$.
model_solution:
Step 1: Subtract 0.1y from both sides of the first equation and add 0.2x to both sides of the first equation to get: \begin{align*} 2.2x-2.1y&=-3.2,\\ x&=0.6x-y+8.8 \end{align*}
Step 2: Multiply the second equation by 2 to get: \begin{align*} 2.2x-2.1y&=-3.2\\ 1.2x-2y&=17.6 \end{align*}
Subtract the first equation from the second equation to get: 
$-0.0x+0.9y=20.8$
Divide both sides of the equation by 0.9 to get: 

$y=23.08888$
Step 3: Substitute $y = 23.08888$ into the second equation $x = 0.6x - y + 8.8$ to get: $x = 0.6x - 23.08888 + 8.8$.
Subtract 0.6x from both sides of the equation to get: $0.4x = -14.28808$.
Divide both sides of the equation by 0.4 to get: x = -35.72
Substitute y = 23.08888 into the first equation 2.2x - 2.1y = -3.2 to get: 2.2x - 2.1(23.08888) = -3.2.
Substitute y = 23.08888 into the first equation 2.2x - 2.1(23.08888) = -3.2 to get: 2.2x - 48.385316 = -3.2.
Add 48.385316 to both sides of the equation to get: 2.2x = 45.185316.
